From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 18:45:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX-015 Route B rd_native gpu_culling
 in-frame compute cull (R1 Rurix-owned scratch indirect buffer)

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040..0045. First rd_native pass that itself issues an
RD::buffer_copy + RD::buffer_clear. R1 REVISION of the device-removal root cause
(passes/gpu_culling/rd_native_device_removal_diagnosis.md): the first-shipped
0046 buffer_clear'd + compute UAV-wrote Godot's LIVE multimesh->command_buffer
while the SAME frame's native draw_list_draw_indirect consumed it as a
DrawIndexedInstanced indirect argument. That same-frame dual role is a GPU-side
execution fault the D3D12 draw-graph does not synchronize (device removal,
0x887A0005 — an asynchronous GPU-side fault, NOT a CPU-side validation error;
confirmed silent under BOTH the plain debug layer and GPU-Based Validation). An
empty kernel with the identical binding surface and a 1-instance scene both still
removed the device, so the cause is the buffer's dual role, not the kernel / OOB
/ b0 layout / RAW-vs-structured binding. RD::barrier/full_barrier are deprecated
no-ops, so the fix must be structural.

R1 decouples the dual role onto a RURIX-OWNED scratch indirect-args buffer and
NEVER touches the live command buffer with compute/clear:

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_gpu_culling_rd_native(RID transforms, RID commands, RID
  scratch_commands, RID visibility, const uint8_t *frustum_planes, uint32_t
  planes_bytes, const uint8_t *b0, uint32_t b0_bytes, uint32_t instance_count,
  uint32_t surface_count, uint32_t command_stride_dwords, uint32_t
  instance_count_dword_index, uint32_t visibility_bytes, uint32_t command_bytes).
  Takes Godot RID handles. `commands` is the LIVE buffer (buffer_copy READ source
  only); `scratch_commands` is the caller-owned scratch the cull writes.
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings
  (.../passes/gpu_culling/backend int default 0 and .../rd_container_path),
  INDEPENDENT of the four shim gpu_culling settings (0027-0029), untouched.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_gpu_culling_rd_native
  override + a self-owned 96-byte frustum-planes SSBO (t1). Lazily builds the
  pipeline from the Rurix container, buffer_update's the planes, then (R1)
  buffer_copy's the p_command_bytes live command template into the SCRATCH buffer,
  buffer_clear's ONLY the SCRATCH buffer's per-surface count dword + the bitmask
  BEFORE opening its own compute list, binds t0=transforms / t1=planes /
  u0=SCRATCH_commands / u1=visibility, and dispatches ceil(instance_count/64). The
  live command buffer is never cleared / never UAV-bound.
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/forward_clustered/render_forward_clustered.{h,cpp}:
  a new backend == 2 call-site (sibling of the untouched shim path). Collects the
  frame's indirect MultiMeshes, builds the normal-negated 96-byte t1 planes
  payload (n_rurix = -normal, d_rurix = plane.d — the Godot Plane sign red line)
  and the 48-byte b0, lazily allocates the Rurix visibility bitmask AND (R1) a
  Rurix-owned scratch indirect-args buffer per base (storage_buffer_create with
  DISPATCH_INDIRECT usage, sized like the live command buffer), and offers each to
  the module. On a successful record the base->scratch entry is put in a per-frame
  map (rurix_cull_rdn_active_scratch, rebuilt every _render_scene), and the
  indirect draw site (_render_list_template) RETARGETS draw_list_draw_indirect to
  read the scratch buffer for that base (falling back to the native command buffer
  for any base not recorded this frame — the is_empty() short-circuit keeps the
  default path a single branch).

The container line (co-located under passes/gpu_culling/artifacts) is UNCHANGED:
the HLSL kernel gpu_culling_rd_native.hlsl (frustum planes in a t1
StructuredBuffer<float4>, 48-byte b0), the Rurix-owned RTS0, the descriptor
layout, the generate_rd_container.py PASS_REGISTRY entry, and
out/gpu_culling_rd_native.rd_container.bin (DXC + DXV green, verify_container
59/59). R1 changes ONLY which RID is bound as u0 and which RID the draw reads —
NO container / b0 / kernel / RTS0 recompile.

CAVEAT (also in the pass manifest): R1 is a CANDIDATE, not a proven fix. If the
device-removal is a general RDG limitation for "a draw-indirect buffer written by
compute and consumed in the same frame" (rather than something specific to
Godot's out-of-graph command-buffer state management), a fully-Rurix-owned buffer
will hit the SAME wall. R1 therefore ships only after
ci/grx_rb_gpu_culling_rd_native_enablement_smoke.py shows NO device removal on
real hardware; until then real_gpu_pass stays false and the pass stays
default-disabled.

Fail-closed everywhere: default backend == 0 (and empty container path, or any
allocation/copy/bind/pipeline failure incl. a missing scratch buffer) never
engages the cull; a failed record is a no-op (the native CPU-written command
buffer keeps driving the draw). Additive pass — no native Godot compute pass is
replaced. Because the cull is conservative (never culls a visible instance), the
on-screen image is identical to native; only the GPU draw-side instance count is
reduced. RXGD_ABI_VERSION unchanged (no C ABI struct change, no RxGdCaps.flags
bit; bridge-independent). No performance claim is made.
